<paragraph blockId="7.[812,1457,471,848]" box="[813,878,471,497]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">NOTE</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[812,1457,471,848]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">
The closest relative of this species is 
<taxonomicName box="[1216,1328,503,529]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis box="[1216,1328,503,529]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">C. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[1343,1455,503,529]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis box="[1343,1455,503,529]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">C. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed by having elliptic-obovate leaves, 30-60 × 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" unit="mm" value="30.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="20.0">20- 40 mm</quantity>
, base widely to narrowly cuneate, upper surface midgreen; petiole 
<quantity box="[972,1080,598,625]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5-10 mm</quantity>
; lax inflorescence, 6-20- flowered inflorescence and peduncle up to 
<quantity box="[1172,1254,630,657]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
. While 
<taxonomicName box="[1331,1453,630,657]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellipticus">
<emphasis box="[1331,1453,630,657]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">C. ellipticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by having orbicular- elliptic leaves (20-40 × 
<quantity box="[812,934,694,721]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" unit="mm" value="27.0" valueMax="34.0" valueMin="20.0">20-34 mm</quantity>
), base widely obtuse to rounded, upper surface dark bluish green; petiole 
<quantity box="[1102,1195,726,752]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4-7 mm</quantity>
; compact inflorescence, 5-13- flowered inflorescence and peduncle up to 
<quantity box="[1387,1456,758,784]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[822,885,790,816]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="10.[132,143,1986,2003]" captionTargetBox="[193,1383,215,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-29@10.[193,1384,215,1803]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIG. 6. — Cotoneaster ellipticus (Lindl.) Hort ex Loudon outline (A) and close up of leaves (B) and fruit (C). Collection number: Memariani, Zangooei &amp; Arjmandi 43358 (FUMH); determined by Raei Niaki &amp; Attar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6573125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6573125/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). This species occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[1152,1246,790,816]" name="Pakistan" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, Kashmir (
<bibRefCitation author="FRYER J. &amp; HYLMO B." pageId="7" pageNumber="146" refId="ref4629" refString="FRYER J. &amp; HYLMO B. 2009. - Cotoneasters: A Comprehensive Guide to Shrubs for Flowers, Fruit, and Foliage. Timber press, Portland, London, 344 p." type="book" year="2009">Fryer &amp; Hylmö 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[1018,1066,822,848]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
